            <title>[THRIFT-4606] LGPL license file still present </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4606</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3209&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3209&lt;/a&gt;&#160;it was noted that references to the LGPL&#160;could be removed. &#160;However, in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/debian/copyright#L124&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/debian/copyright#L124&lt;/a&gt;&#160;there is still a reference to the license, which now lives at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/doc/licenses/lgpl-2.1.txt.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/doc/licenses/lgpl-2.1.txt.&lt;/a&gt;&#160; If I&apos;m reading &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3209&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3209&lt;/a&gt;&#160;correctly, both&#160;the reference to LGPL and the LGPL license file itself can be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
